The National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, China's top political advisory body, held a news conference on Friday, one day ahead of the opening of its annual session. Guo Weimin, spokesperson of the first session of the 14th CPPCC National Committee, briefed journalists on the session and took questions. Here are some highlights: - The session will open at 3 pm Saturday and close on March 11 The 14th National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference will open its first session on Saturday at 3 pm at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing. (Read more)